<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="162" pageId="8" pageNumber="159" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1796,2037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1796,1821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
FEMALE. This species can be separated from other species of group 2 by the following combination of characters: frons and vertex with weak and long carina medially, but without any grooves; scutellar scale narrow, as broad as diameter of nearby punctures, posteriorly turning into median longitudinal carina extending through propodeal face; T1 without apical band of setae; S1 yellowish red; T2 and S2 polished among punctures and strongly shining; S2–S3 each with apical narrow band of dense, appressed pale golden setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1796,2037]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1437,151,861]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="162" pageId="8" pageNumber="159">Head black; mandible reddish yellow except apex black; frons covered with black setae; vertex, gena, clypeus and mandible covered with pale golden setae. In dorsal view, outline of head obtrapezoidal with anterior margin not protruding, 1.5 times wider than long; lateral margins strongly convergent posteriorly behind eye; posterior margin truncate. In lateral view, head longitudinally elongated; frons flat; gena narrow in lateral view with GOI = 1.84. Eye protruding from frons. Mandible with two inner denticles. Scape and pedicel reddish yellow; flagellum black dorsally, reddish yellow ventrally; F1 tinged with reddish yellow; F10 conical with apex compressed but not concave. Palpi yellow ventrally, dark brown dorsally. Mesosoma entirely yellowish red; dorsal face covered with black setae; lateral and ventral face with pale golden setae; lateral margins subparallel. Legs reddish yellow except tarsi, apex of mid- and hind femora and tibiae reddish brown. Metasoma oval, black except S1 yellowish red, entirely covered with pale golden setae; T2, 4 and 5 also covered with black setae; minimum distance between drop-shaped, basal median spot and apical band of T2 twice the breadth of the spot; T2 with golden felt line laterally, lateral length of T2:length of felt line = 100:40; S2–S6 each with apical fringe of long pale golden setae; T2 broadly and shallowly depressed medially; S1 with median longitudinal carina. MALE. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
