<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="162" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,151,861]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,655,680]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lelej, A. S." box="[321,460,655,680]" journalOrPublisher="Yamane (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). Tropics" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="91 – 104" part="6" publicationUrl="10.3759/tropics.6.91" refString="Lelej, A. S. (1996) Mutillid wasps collected in Malaysia and Indonesia by Dr. Sk. Yamane (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). Tropics, 6 (1 - 2), 91 - 104. https: // doi. org / 10.3759 / tropics. 6.91" title="Mutillid wasps collected in Malaysia and Indonesia by Dr. Sk" type="journal article" year="1996">Lelej (1996)</bibRefCitation>
noted that this species may be the female of 
<taxonomicName authority="Invrea, 1943" authorityName="Invrea" authorityYear="1943" box="[960,1287,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gribodoana">
<emphasis box="[960,974,656,679]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[988,1119,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">gribodoana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Invrea, F." box="[1133,1279,656,680]" journalOrPublisher="Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" pagination="191 - 193" part="61" refString="Invrea, F. (1943) A proposito di una Smicromyrme del'Isola di Borneo nota tassonomica e combiamento di nome (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, 61, 191 - 193." title="A proposito di una Smicromyrme del'Isola di Borneo nota tassonomica e combiamento di nome (Hymenoptera, Mutillidae)" type="journal article" year="1943">Invrea, 1943</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1995" box="[271,456,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belokobylskiji">
<emphasis box="[271,285,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[300,456,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">belokobylskiji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mickel" authorityYear="1937" box="[512,611,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petina">
<emphasis box="[512,526,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[541,611,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">petina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
other than 
<taxonomicName authority="Okayasu, 2017" authorityName="Okayasu" authorityYear="2017" box="[741,874,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="calopoda" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[741,755,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[770,874,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">calopoda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[882,973,692,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[882,973,692,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Okayasu, 2017" authorityName="Okayasu" authorityYear="2017" box="[1029,1181,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ohbayashii" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1029,1043,692,715]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1058,1181,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">ohbayashii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1189,1280,692,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1189,1280,692,717]" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having the characters of group 2. However, it can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mickel" authorityYear="1937" box="[841,939,728,751]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petina">
<emphasis box="[841,855,728,751]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[869,939,728,751]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">petina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pale golden setae on vertex (black in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mickel" authorityYear="1937" box="[151,221,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petina">
<emphasis box="[151,221,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">petina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and having apical narrow band of setae on S2–S3 (lacking in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mickel" authorityYear="1937" box="[930,1000,765,788]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="petina">
<emphasis box="[930,1000,765,788]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">petina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1995" box="[1132,1315,764,788]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belokobylskiji">
<emphasis box="[1132,1146,764,787]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1159,1315,764,788]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">belokobylskiji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by narrow scutellar scale (wide in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1995" box="[417,573,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belokobylskiji">
<emphasis box="[417,573,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">belokobylskiji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the weak depression on T2 (strong in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lelej" authorityYear="1995" box="[1021,1176,800,824]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Sinotilla" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="belokobylskiji">
<emphasis box="[1021,1176,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="162">belokobylskiji</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), and the smaller body size.
</paragraph>
